Vice President Kamala Harris visited a recreation center in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania to discuss the importance of the Child Tax Credit included in the American Rescue Plan. She emphasized that the Child Tax Credit will lift half of America's children out of poverty and highlighted the increased and expanded benefits of the credit. Harris also urged families to take action to receive the monthly payments starting in July by visiting ChildTaxCredit.gov. She stressed the administration's commitment to supporting families and uplifting children in the community.